trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> objects.
All objects which derive from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> have a <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> named
<xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> class using the items in the specified <xref href="System.Collections.IList"></xref>.
The collection whose items are copied to the new <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> to this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The binding to add to the collection.
0, if the operation was successful (note that this is not the index of the added item).
commandBinding is **null**.
Adds the items of the specified <xref href="System.Collections.ICollection"></xref> to the end of this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The collection of items to add to the end of this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The collection to add is `null`.
Removes all items from this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
Determines whether the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> is in this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The binding to locate in the collection.
**true** if the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> is in the collection; otherwise, **false**.
Copies all of the items in the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> to the specified one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.
The array into which the collection is copied.
The index position in commandBindings at which copying starts.
commandBindings is `null`.
index is less than 0.
Gets the number of <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> items in this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The number of bindings in the collection.
Gets an enumerator that iterates through this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The enumerator for this collection.
Searches for the first occurrence of the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> in this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The binding to locate in the collection.
The index of the first occurrence of value, if found; otherwise, -1.
Inserts the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> into this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> at the specified index.
The zero-based index at which to insert commandBinding
The binding to insert.
commandBinding is `null`.
Gets a value indicating whether this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> has a fixed size.
A <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> is never a fixed size; therefore, <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection.IsFixedSize%2A> will always return **false**.
**true** if the collection has a fixed size; otherwise, **false**.
The default value is **false**.
Gets a value indicating whether this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> is read-only.
A <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> is never read-only; therefore, <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection.IsReadOnly%2A> will always return `false`.
`true` if the collection is read-only; otherwise, `false`.
The default value is `false`.
Gets a value indicating whether access to this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref> is synchronized (thread-safe).
<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection.SyncRoot%2A> can be used to synchronize access to the collection.
`true` if the collection is thread-safe; otherwise, `false`.
The default value is `false`.
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> at the specified index.
The position in the collection.
The binding at the specified index.
Removes the first occurrence of the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> from this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The binding to remove.
Removes the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> at the specified index of this <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The zero-based index of the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding"></xref> to remove.
Gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
An object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.ICollection.CopyTo(System.Array,System.Int32)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> interface.
A zero-based <xref href="System.Array"></xref> that receives the copied items from the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The first position in the specified <xref href="System.Array"></xref> to receive the copied contents.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Add(System.Object)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.

The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to add to the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The position into which the new element was inserted.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Contains(System.Object)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to locate in the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextEffectCollection"></xref>.
`true` if the <xref href="System.Object"></xref> is found in the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>; otherwise, `false`.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.IndexOf(System.Object)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to locate in the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
The index of value if found in the list; otherwise, -1.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Insert(System.Int32,System.Object)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The zero-based index at which to insert the <xref href="System.Object"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to insert into the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Item(System.Int32)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The zero-based index of the element to get or set.
The element at the specified index.
For a description of this member, see <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Remove(System.Object)"></xref>.
This member is an explicit interface member implementation.
It can be used only when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection> instance is cast to an <xref:System.Collections.IList> interface.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to remove from the <xref href="System.Windows.Input.CommandBindingCollection"></xref>.
